----------

TypeScript is a statically typed language that provides type safety and interoperability with JavaScript. Duck typing is a concept that allows objects to be treated as if they were of a certain type, based on their methods or properties. By combining the type safety of TypeScript with the flexibility of duck typing, developers can write more maintainable and scalable code.

